Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.35,0:01:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The attacks by the Gundams\Nsent by the Space Colonies...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...reflected the colonies'\Nretaliatory intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.79,0:01:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ has masked its identity\Nin the Alliance Military...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.30,0:01:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...and the Gundams' mission\Nis to attack them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.67,0:01:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The year is After Colony 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.58,0:01:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ has finally taken\Ncenter stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.08,0:01:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,With an army of elite soldiers\Nat his command...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:01:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,...Treize Khushrenada plans to\Ndestroy the Alliance Military.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.35,0:02:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The battle between OZ and the\Nmobile suits sent to Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.09,0:02:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,...causes serious repercussions\Non the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.09,0:02:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where it starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.20,0:02:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes to every family member,\Nseeking their verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.40,0:02:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything he does is thorough\Nand well thought out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.34,0:02:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.27,0:02:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You obviously just wanna\Ntake the easy way out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.54,0:02:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only way I can live.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.60,0:02:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Last stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.57,0:02:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.67,0:02:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive yourself for\Naccidentally killing a pacifist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.68,0:02:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it happened because\Nyou were tricked by OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:03:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I can sympathize.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.18,0:03:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But to put your life in the\Nhands of your victim's family...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.32,0:03:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Going from place to place...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.54,0:03:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...I knew it'd only be a matter\Nof time before someone found us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.64,0:03:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.01,0:03:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't overdo it\Nin your state.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.91,0:03:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.55,0:03:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.83,0:03:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,H-hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.28,0:04:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks; I owe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.18,0:04:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.15,0:04:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're gonna transport this,\Nwe can't do it by land.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.02,0:04:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- Then by sea...\N- I've got my eye on a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.15,0:04:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we know that\Nwe're being watched.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.92,0:04:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So it might be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.52,0:04:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use my carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.99,0:04:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect you to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first time we've met\Nface to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.74,0:05:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Lucrezia Noin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.77,0:05:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I serve under Colonel Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.61,0:05:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.87,0:05:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilot you fought\Nagainst in Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think we won't\Nput up a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.25,0:05:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Zechs wants to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He does?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.95,0:05:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,To try pumping us for\Ninformation or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.45,0:05:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't misunderstand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.26,0:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not speaking\Nas an OZ soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.99,0:05:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to see you as\Na fellow mobile suit pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.36,0:05:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He hopes for another chance\Nto fight you boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.73,0:05:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants a final match?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.67,0:05:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like an admirable guy,\Nthis Zechs fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.30,0:05:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you guys,\Nwhether or not you believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.77,0:05:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.01,0:05:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna trust her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.71,0:05:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not the kind of guy\Nto plant a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.71,0:05:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.82,0:05:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then my mobile suit will\Ncome in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.52,0:05:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't confirmed if the pilot\Nof the self-detonated Gundam...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.19,0:05:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...at the Siberia Base is\Ndead or alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.93,0:06:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been trying to reach\NColonel Zechs...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.10,0:06:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...the OZ pilot that fought\Nthe Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.97,0:06:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems he's already moved\Nfrom the Lake Victoria base...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.94,0:06:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...and I can't reach him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.37,0:06:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So we still don't know anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.74,0:06:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I've been able to\Nfind out one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.38,0:06:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.41,0:06:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Zechs did something\Nhighly peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Peculiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.02,0:06:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,After the battle in Siberia...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.92,0:06:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,...Colonel Zechs ordered a large\Namount of Gundanium...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.59,0:06:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,...shipped from outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.56,0:06:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To reconstruct the Gundam\Nfrom the remains they collected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I know he was ordered\Nto destroy the Gundam...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.10,0:06:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...because OZ found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.97,0:06:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there are signs...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.14,0:06:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,...that the Gundam which was\Ndestroyed might've been a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.54,0:06:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So much Gundanium alloy\Nwas shipped...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.81,0:06:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...they'd easily be able to make\Ntwo mobile suits out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So they used a portion\Nto build the fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.62,0:06:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they're using the rest\Nto reconstruct the Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.32,0:06:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes that Gundam\Nso special, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants one final match\Nto decide things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.99,0:07:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He's that kind of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.20,0:07:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirteen years ago,\Nwhen he was about six...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.33,0:07:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...I faced him in\Na fencing match.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.29,0:07:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He hates his opponent\Nhaving a handicap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.30,0:07:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know Colonel Zechs?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.60,0:07:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a hero in the eyes\Nof the Peacecrafts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.20,0:07:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many stories\Nof his bravery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.97,0:07:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could get in touch\Nwith Colonel Zechs...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.18,0:07:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...then I might find out\Nwhat happened to Heero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:08:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like someone else\Nis looking for Heero Yuy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.65,0:08:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Who it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.85,0:08:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Noventa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.75,0:08:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Noventa?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.79,0:08:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.59,0:08:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wife of Marshal Noventa, the\NAlliance's Chief Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.56,0:08:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...who was killed by your\NGundam friend at New Edwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.40,0:08:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She's trying to keep her\Nsearch a secret from OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.07,0:08:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to contact\NMrs. Noventa right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.84,0:08:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.81,0:08:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you he'd be alive,\Ndidn't I Noin?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.45,0:08:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's got a strong will to live.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.62,0:08:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.59,0:08:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And sorry to drag you\Ninto this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.69,0:08:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't forget that I'm{\i0}\N{\i1}a mobile suit pilot too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.16,0:08:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I understand your feelings{\i0}\N{\i1}to a certain extent.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you Noin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.66,0:08:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch your step around\Nthat search party.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Given this situation I won't\Nbe able to help you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to somehow\Ndeceive them on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.11,0:08:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll take care of it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.77,0:09:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over and out.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.74,0:09:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We must make the final\Nmodifications to Zero One...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.88,0:09:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,...before they get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There are numerous rumors...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.92,0:09:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...that the Gundam destroyed\Nby Colonel Zechs was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.66,0:09:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we allow Colonel Zechs\Nto continue acting on his own?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.30,0:09:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This Zechs issue is becoming\Nquite a topic within Romefeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.91,0:09:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.95,0:09:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.34,0:10:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A search party from Lake\NVictoria is in pursuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.27,0:10:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But Zechs would never do\Nanything to cause me trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.88,0:10:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's worrying about\Nthis too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was one of OZ's carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.76,0:10:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.69,0:10:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's a good chance\Nthey're aboard the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Think we should just leave them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.50,0:10:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.43,0:10:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're bound to show\Ntheir true colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.33,0:10:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't lose sight of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.44,0:10:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.31,0:10:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let them have\Ntheir way this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.63,0:10:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the left arm be\Nautomatically balanced...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,...for the extra weight?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.30,0:11:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I purposely avoided that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.57,0:11:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead I've had it\Nat my fingertips...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.90,0:11:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...so I'll have a speed\Nadvantage during battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.87,0:11:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing them working hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.68,0:11:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not different from\Nany other young pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.62,0:11:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We could keep Colonel Zechs\Nfrom getting into any danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.09,0:11:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...by getting rid of them\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You still don't understand him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.26,0:11:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs would never forgive us\Nif we did such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.36,0:11:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the shield been attached\Nto the Gatling arm too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.76,0:11:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but it's heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.60,0:11:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.00,0:11:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally we wouldn't let others\Ntouch our own mobile suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.77,0:11:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you'd better hurry up\Nand get to know this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.51,0:11:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.54,0:11:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time I'll defeat Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.22,0:12:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I contacted Mrs. Noventa,\Nand she's forwarded this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.49,0:12:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She said she'd like you\Nto deliver the letter for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.23,0:12:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Noventa?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.83,0:12:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's made out to\NMr. Heero Yuy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.40,0:12:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To Heero?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.57,0:12:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your sudden visit caught\Nme off guard..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.28,0:12:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and I didn't feel that{\i0}\N{\i1}I was able...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.52,0:12:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...to express the true feelings{\i0}\N{\i1}in my heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.29,0:12:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's why I decided to{\i0}\N{\i1}write this letter.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.46,0:12:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You made a mistake when{\i0}\N{\i1}your plan went awry in battle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.39,0:12:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But stop suffering over it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.56,0:12:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My husband and Ventei died{\i0}\N{\i1}trying to build a world...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...where genuine young men{\i0}\N{\i1}like yourselves...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...could live happily.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.40,0:13:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have no regrets.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's what happens in war.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.11,0:13:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A wrong turn in the past{\i0}\N{\i1}can be painful for anyone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But you people are still young!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.88,0:13:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hope you'll think about{\i0}\N{\i1}building a new future!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.99,0:13:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our family is honored{\i0}\N{\i1}to have met with you!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"I pray the day will arrive\Nwhen all battles cease."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.13,0:13:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"To my dear friend,\NMr. Heero Yuy."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.40,0:13:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So Heero's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.30,0:13:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew he'd be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.90,0:13:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm leaving for Sicily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.57,0:13:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll meet Mrs. Noventa\Nand ask where Heero is!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.47,0:13:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.11,0:13:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make flight arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.61,0:13:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero was alive after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.02,0:13:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't have our special\Nguests catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:13:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Put these on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.54,0:14:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.30,0:14:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The South Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.64,0:14:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A mobile suit battle on\Na continent covered in ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.88,0:14:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only place to have\Na battle and go unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.95,0:14:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.22,0:14:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All areas needed to determine\Nability have been restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.02,0:14:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Measuring abilities isn't\Nenough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.22,0:14:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I want this Gundam\Ncompletely restored!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we take it that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna know more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.83,0:14:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,More about this mobile suit,\Nand more about its pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.10,0:14:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to completely\Nrestore the right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.51,0:14:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs power to handle\Nthe giant beam cannon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.81,0:14:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,...and a system to precisely\Ncontrol the beam saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.84,0:14:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd need enough time to\Nbuild a whole new mobile suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.58,0:14:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at least complete the\Nbeam saber system...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.05,0:14:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...using parts from the left\Narm of Tallgeese.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.19,0:15:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Zechs, what are you\Ntrying to prove?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.86,0:15:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, just try to indulge me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.83,0:15:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.33,0:15:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.70,0:15:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,New instructions for the\Nrestoration of Zero One's right arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.17,0:15:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Problem, Lieutenant!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.41,0:15:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Our craft is being followed\Nby a number of carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.14,0:15:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They've found us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.45,0:15:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We spotted them when\Nwe reached the continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.18,0:15:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They've calculated our\Nflying range.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.58,0:15:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They must've realized we'd be\Nheaded for Colonel Zechs' base.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.95,0:15:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll throw them off\Nby changing directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.59,0:15:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.42,0:15:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If we sacrifice two Aries,\Nwe could break free of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.19,0:15:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then even if they know the\Nbase location we can attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.30,0:15:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't do anything\Nto burden Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.87,0:15:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going on the Aries?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.97,0:15:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be overpowered\Nby their numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.38,0:15:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My mission is to get you\Nto the destination safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.01,0:15:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The method is up to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.42,0:16:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Two Aries suits have been{\i0}\N{\i1}dropped and are free-falling.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.63,0:16:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They haven't righted{\i0}\N{\i1}themselves yet!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't be tricked by{\i0}\N{\i1}their pranks!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.60,0:16:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll release our suits too!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.14,0:16:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.94,0:16:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Roger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.05,0:16:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Carrier One's going down!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.35,0:16:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Spread out!{\i0}\N{\i1}- Roger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.13,0:16:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,One more shot and Carrier\NTwo's down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.41,0:16:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back in the clouds\Nand be patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.48,0:17:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, I'm going for it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.82,0:17:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.71,0:17:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sorry!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.57,0:17:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That was careless.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.48,0:17:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.58,0:17:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Backup troops?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.19,0:17:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This time take me directly\Nto Zechs and the Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll cover for you,{\i0}\N{\i1}Lieutenant Noin!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.87,0:18:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Get outta here while{\i0}\N{\i1}you can!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.74,0:18:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't be ridiculous!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.68,0:18:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.91,0:18:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.88,0:18:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to rescue\NLieutenant Noin!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.11,0:18:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's against orders.\N- What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.42,0:18:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't take that crap from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.82,0:18:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn us around!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.79,0:18:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.76,0:18:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's enough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.07,0:18:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We surrender!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.20,0:18:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's no point continuing!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.27,0:18:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We've thrown down our weapons!\NWe surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.44,0:18:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop attacking us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think the normal\Nrules apply...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...to someone who's betrayed\NRomefeller?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.02,0:18:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I might consider it, if you\Nhand over the Gundam...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.55,0:18:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...as proof of Zechs' betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.29,0:18:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.66,0:18:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately that won't\Nchange Zechs destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.53,0:18:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll finish him off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.76,0:19:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As my reward for\Ndefeating him...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.33,0:19:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...my superior skills\Nwill be recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.60,0:19:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let you get near Zechs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.04,0:19:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So Zechs is here after all!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.04,0:19:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.17,0:19:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay, we've got our info.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.64,0:19:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Get rid of them!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.32,0:19:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You came back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.09,0:19:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency landing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.36,0:19:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me off first!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll correct the mistakes\Nyour weakness caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.96,0:20:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.23,0:20:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Gundam Zero Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.23,0:20:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That Gundam's strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.44,0:20:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.58,0:20:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundam will be used as\Nan excuse to get the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.88,0:20:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can't let anyone report\Nthat it was seen here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.97,0:20:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fighting Zechs' soldiers{\i0}\N{\i1}off at Point 103...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.70,0:20:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...of the South Pole.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.51,0:20:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've located...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.47,0:20:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...a Gundam!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.34,0:20:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Those who've laid eyes on\Na Gundam shall not live."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.35,0:20:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are my orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.52,0:21:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.86,0:21:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,THERE'S A GUNDAM DOWN HERE!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.84,0:21:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.41,0:21:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I have to keep\Non fighting like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.22,0:21:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,These young pilots are too pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.30,0:21:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.60,0:21:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The name is Trowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.80,0:21:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to reload\Nthe explosives for Heero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.57,0:21:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.38,0:22:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop worrying about that\Nright now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.61,0:22:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Start thinking about\Nyour own welfare!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.48,0:23:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs waits at the South Pole\Nwith the completed Wing Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.49,0:23:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero challenges Zechs to a duel\Nwith Trowa's Gundam Heavyarms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.42,0:23:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero and Zechs commence their\Nbattle amidst the snowy winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.46,0:23:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs tries to find something\Nbeyond the desperate battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.37,0:23:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As does Noin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.80,0:23:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Relena arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.87,0:23:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 16,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.78,0:23:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Sorrowful Battle".
